  "datePublished": "2026-03-06",
  "description": "Play is voluntary, intrinsically motivated activity pursued for its own sake. It is broader than games: a child stacking blocks is playing without rules, objectives, or competition. Play becomes a game when it acquires structure — [rules](./rules.md), objectives, constraints — but the underlying quality of voluntary engagement persists.",
